OL,7,FWriting in, she described Hester's
OL,8,Fwords as "outrageously racist and
OL,9,Fsexist" and added that "the Tory party
OL,10,Fhas long been a source of whipping up
OL,11,Fracism in this country".
OL,13,FSomething she echoed when speaking
OL,14,Fabout the Labour party, stating:
OL,15,F"shocking levels of racism and sexism
OL,16,Ffrom within the Labour party, again
OL,17,Fmuch of it directed against me
OL,18,Fpersonally".
